Timbals with 4 long ribs; rib 4 shorter than ribs 1 to 3 ; ribs 1 to 3 fused ventrally, but all 4 long ribs fused dorsally with well developed basal spur;
3 intercalary
ribs short and generally thin; dome on timbal plate elongated with parallel shallow grooves and ridges running across dome; basal dome prominent; anterior part of timbals mostly occupied by ribs.
